# --- Windows native deployment build outputs ---
# NOTE: the top-level `build/` and `dist/` rules above are aimed at
# Python sdist/wheel/PyInstaller outputs. For the Windows native
# deployment we WANT the following committed so that operators can
# `git pull` on a fresh Windows Server and run install.ps1 directly
# without a separate binary transfer channel. We therefore re-include
# them explicitly (order matters: these must sit after the generic
# build/ and dist/ rules).
#
# Keep ignored:
#   - windows/.build-venv/       PyInstaller throwaway venv (~200MB)
#   - windows/build/build/       PyInstaller intermediate work dir
#   - windows/build/dist/        PyInstaller intermediate onefile dir
windows/.build-venv/

# Re-include the Windows deployment source + shipped binaries.
!windows/build/
!windows/build/**
!windows/dist/
!windows/dist/**
!windows/release/
!windows/release/**

# Still ignore PyInstaller intermediate trees that land under
# windows/build/ when build-relay.ps1 runs (the final exe is moved
# into windows/dist/ before commit).
windows/build/build/
windows/build/dist/
